NavigationHistoryEntryId.summary:
The id read-only property of the
interface returns the id of the history entry. This is a unique, UA-generated value that always represents a specific history entry, useful to correlate it with an external resource such as a storage cache.

remarks.para: This differs from the of a history entry. The key is a unique, UA-generated value that represents the history entry's slot in the entries list rather than the entry itself. It is used to navigate that particular slot via . The key will be reused by other entries that replace the entry in the list (that is, if the is replace).
